\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534323\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534323\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yxt1665702612061.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yxt1665702612061.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yxt1665702612061.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yxt1665702612061\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n         \n Constructing Forms and Reports\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Forms are presentation components used in desktop applications and reports are used for printing. They are created in the same way.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"yxt1665702612061__li_d12083e1_d12084e1_d12085e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create the form or report component. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nlq1704964362863.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nlq1704964362863.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create a new component.\">Create a New Component</a>.\n           </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"yxt1665702612061__li_d12086e1_d12087e1_d12088e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Define the data structure and basic layout of the component in the Define Frames worksheet. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cvl1690356504825.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvl1690356504825.html\" title=\"Use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically define both the component data structure and the layout of the component.\">Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports</a>.\n           </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"yxt1665702612061__li_d12089e1_d12090e1_d12091e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Refine the layout and appearance of the component in the Define Frames worksheet:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yxt1665702612061__li_d12092e1_d12093e1_d12094e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lfh1665702612528.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lfh1665702612528.html\" title=\"Use the Define Frames worksheet to refine the layout of the form component.\">Design the Layout of Forms</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yxt1665702612061__li_d12095e1_d12096e1_d12097e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"erz1665702688168.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/erz1665702688168.html\" title=\"Use the Define Frames worksheet to refine the layout of the Report component. You can add header and footer frames to define pages headers and footers, and break frames to control page break behavior.\">Design the Layout of Reports</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"yxt1665702612061__li_d12098e1_d12099e1_d12100e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"yxt1665702612061__p_d24308e1_d24309e1_d24310e1\">Script the component behavior in the Write Script\n               worksheet. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"btl1705400316529.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/btl1705400316529.html\" title=\"Use the Write Script worksheet to script the component's functionality, include the actions it executes, the way it responds to events, the validation it performs when data is loaded or stored, and so on.\">Script the Component Behavior</a>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For both derived and non-derived entities and fields, you can define script\n                  modules to control component-specific behavior. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gtm1665702624482.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gtm1665702624482.html\" title=\"A script module is a named collection of ProcScript belonging to a development object. Script modules are analogous to events and methods in other programming languages.\">Script Modules</a>. </p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"yxt1665702612061__li_d12101e1_d12102e1_d12103e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span>. This generates a runtime object in your <span class=\"ph filepath\">/project/resources/frm</span> directory.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"yxt1665702612061__li_d12104e1_d12105e1_d12106e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"yxt1665702612061__p_d24311e1_d24312e1_d24313e1\">Test the component. From the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Actions</span> menu, choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Test</span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">This spawns a separate process and activates the exec operation of the component.\n                  When the component exits, control returns to the Uniface IDE.</p>\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"yxt1665702612061__note_w322ab1b5b1c11b3b3_w323ab1b5b1c11b3_w324ab1b5b1c11_w325ab1b5b1_w326ab1b5_w327ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> You can optionally specify test\n      logicals in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.asn</span> file to customize the test environment, providing\n      command line switches that override the default behavior. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nyk1665702685792.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nyk1665702685792.html\" title=\"Test logicals enable you to customize the command used to spawn a component for testing using the Actions &gt;Test option in the Component Editor.\">IDE Test Logicals</a>. </div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qed1665702869715.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Forms</a><p>Form components provide the user interface for Uniface desktop applications. They are always executed on the client system and can be modal (form retains focus until it is closed) or non-modal (users can switch focus to other forms).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wmx1665702870076.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Reports</a><p>Reports are components for generating output—they have no user interface and cannot update the database. They make use of headers, footers, and break frames to format data and control printing.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534323\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534323\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Constructing Forms and Reports Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Constructing Forms and Reports Forms are presentation components used in desktop applications and reports are used for printing. They are created in the same way. Create the form or report component. For more information, see Create a New Component . Define the data structure and basic layout of the component in the Define Frames worksheet. For more information, see Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports . Refine the layout and appearance of the component in the Define Frames worksheet: Design the Layout of Forms Design the Layout of Reports Script the component behavior in the Write Script worksheet. For more information, see Script the Component Behavior . For both derived and non-derived entities and fields, you can define script modules to control component-specific behavior. For more information, see Script Modules . Click Compile . This generates a runtime object in your /project/resources/frm directory. Test the component. From the Actions menu, choose Test . This spawns a separate process and activates the exec operation of the component. When the component exits, control returns to the Uniface IDE. Tip: You can optionally specify test logicals in the ide.asn file to customize the test environment, providing command line switches that override the default behavior. For more information, see IDE Test Logicals . Related Links Forms Form components provide the user interface for Uniface desktop applications. They are always executed on the client system and can be modal (form retains focus until it is closed) or non-modal (users can switch focus to other forms). Reports Reports are components for generating output—they have no user interface and cannot update the database. They make use of headers, footers, and break frames to format data and control printing. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}